Key Match Events: The game came down to the final moments with Wembanyama missing a crucial free throw attempt and Jeremy Sochan missing a potential game-winning three-pointer at the buzzer.
Post-Match Reflections: Victor Wembanyama finished with 34 points on 30 shots, while Harrison Barnes and Devin Vassell added 23 and 22 points, respectively.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Minnesota Timberwolves held off the gritty San Antonio Spurs on Sunday, securing their third consecutive win with a 112-110 victory at Target Center in Minneapolis.
